team"},{"avatar":"https://ee.bytedance.net/ratak/employees/3863359/avatar/?format=noop.png","email":"qizihan@bytedance.com","name":"qizi"},{"avatar":"https://s3-fs.pstatp.com/static-resource/v1/43d80005ffccbded38e9~?image_size=72x72&cut_type=&quality=&format=png&sticker_format=.webp","email":"yeyuanfeng@bytedance.com","name":"yeyuanfeng"}],"scripts":{"test":"RUNTIME_IDC_NAME=lf ../../node_modules/.bin/jest --config ./jest.config.json --coverage --env=node","build":"rm -rf lib && npx tsc","prepublish":"npm run build"},"license":"ISC","dependencies":{"tslib":"^1.9.3"},"dist":{"key":"/@byted-service/metainfo/-/@byted-service/metainfo-1.0.0.tgz","shasum":"daa0e9e99eed9b01f637bb5901854ed829a4207b","size":6342,"tarball":"https://bnpm.byted.org/@byted-service/metainfo/-/metainfo-1.0.0.tgz"},"readmeFilename":"README.md","publish_time":1569564701331,"_npmVersion":"6.11.3","_cnpm_publish_time":1569564701331,"contributors":[{"email":"qizihan@bytedance.com","name":"qizi"}],"version":"1.0.0","_npmUser":{"name":"qizi","email":"qizihan@bytedance.com"},"types":"lib/index.d.ts","repository":{"type":"git","url":"https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/packages/metainfo"},"main":"lib/index.js","_nodeVersion":"12.6.0","files":["lib"],"description":"管理调用链元信息传递的通用模块"},"1.1.7":{"gitHead":"b874c82041dfc2c92881f95f051eacc6c300ef50","readmeFilename":"README.en.md","_nodeVersion":"14.19.3","main":"index.js","description":"管理调用链元信息传递的通用模块","files":["lib"],"readme":"# metainfo\n\n[![bnpm](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/badge/v/@byted-service/metainfo.svg?style=flat-square)](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/package/@byted-service/metainfo) [![download](https://2y8ngapf.fn.bytedance.net/d?p=@byted-service/metainfo)](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/package/@byted-service/metainfo)\n\n[简体中文](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/metainfo/README.md) | [English](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/metainfo/README.en.md) | [CHANGELOG](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/metainfo/CHANGELOG.md)\n\nThis library aligns with `golang`'s `metainfo` library. For specific documents, please see https://code.byted.org/gopkg/metainfo\n\n> If the version is 1.0.2 and below, please upgrade in time to avoid unknown compatibility bugs.\n> Please read this document before use. https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcn2L5x9IgQ4iLEdHofSMPVQc#\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\nnpm install @byted-service/metainfo --registry=http://bnpm.byted.org\n```\n\n## Quick start\n\n```ts\nimport * as MetaInfo from '@byted-service/metainfo';\n\nconst ctx = {};\n\n// Write save chain information in the upstream service call\nMetaInfo.withValue(ctx, 'ROLE', 'AppUser');\n\n// call getValue in downstream service to get call chain information\nMetaInfo.getValue(ctx, 'ROLE'); // \"AppUser\"\n```\n\n## API\n\n### MetaInfo.getValue(ctx, k)\n\nGet the `transient` data of the specified `key` ( including `transient-upstream` data ).\n\n### MetaInfo.getAllValues(ctx)\n\nGet all `transient` data ( including `transient-upstream` data ).\n\n### MetaInfo.withValue(ctx, k, v)\n\nSet `transient` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.delValue(ctx, k)\n\nDelete the `transient` data of the specified `key`.\n\n### MetaInfo.getPersistentValue(ctx, k)\n\nGet the `persistent` data of the specified `key`.\n\n### MetaInfo.getAllPersistentValues(ctx)\n\nGet all `persistent` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.withPersistentValue(ctx, k, v)\n\nSet `persistent` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.delPersistentValue(ctx, k)\n\nDelete the `persistent` data of the specified `key`.\n\n### MetaInfo.transferForward(ctx)\n\nForward pass, used to convert `transient` data from upstream into `transient-upstream` data, and filter out the original `transient-upstream` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.setMetaInfoFromMap(ctx, m)\n\nSave the `metainfo` data in `ctx` to the object for the client to transfer `metainfo` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.saveMetaInfoToMap(ctx, m)\n\nSave the `metainfo` data in the object to `ctx` for the server to receive `metainfo` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.hasMetaInfo(ctx)\n\nDetermine whether there is `metainfo` data in `ctx`.\n\n### MetaInfo.delMetaInfo(ctx)\n\nDelete the `metainfo` data in `ctx`.\n\n### MetaInfo.copyMetaInfo(fromCtx, toCtx)\n\nCopy `metainfo` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.HTTPHeaderToCGIVariable(key)\n\nConvert `HTTP Header` to `CGI key`.\n\n### MetaInfo.CGIVariableToHTTPHeader(key)\n\nConvert `CGI key` to `HTTP Header`.\n\n### MetaInfo.fromHTTPHeader(ctx, h)\n\nObtain `metainfo` from `HTTP Header`.\n\n### MetaInfo.toHTTPHeader(ctx, h)\n\nObtain `HTTP Header` from `metainfo`.\n\n### MetaInfo.withBackwardValues(ctx)\n\nInitialize `backward` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.recvBackwardValue(ctx, key)\n\nGet the `backward` data of the specified `key`.\n\n### MetaInfo.recvAllBackwardValues(ctx)\n\nGet all the `backward` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.setBackwardValue(ctx, key, val)\n\nSet `backward` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.setBackwardValues(ctx, key, val, key, val, ...)\n\nBatch set `backward` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.setBackwardValuesFromMap(ctx, kvs)\n\nBatch set `backward` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.withBackwardValuesToSend(ctx)\n\nInitialize `backward` data ( `send` ).\n\n### MetaInfo.sendBackwardValue(ctx, key, val)\n\nSet `backward` data ( `send` ).\n\n### MetaInfo.sendBackwardValues(ctx, key, val, key, val, ...)\n\nBatch set `backward` data ( `send` ).\n\n### MetaInfo.sendBackwardValuesFromMap(ctx, kvs)\n\nBatch set `backward` data ( `send` ).\n\n### MetaInfo.allBackwardValuesToSend(ctx, kvs)\n\nGet all the `backward` data ( `send` ).\n\n### MetaInfo.turnOffDoubleWrite()\n\nTurn off double write.\n\n### MetaInfo.turnOnDoubleWrite()\n\nTurn on double write.\n\n## Version compatible\n\nIn `version number <= 1.0.2`, the golang metainfo library is not aligned due to historical reasons, and due to its own implementation problems, there are bugs, as follows:\n\n```ts\nimport * as MetaInfo from '@byted-service/metainfo';\n\nconst ctx = {};\n\nMetaInfo.saveTransitValue(ctx, { AAA: 'AAA' });\n\nMetaInfo.getTransitValue(ctx, 'AAA'); // null ???\n```\n\nIn the current version, the dual-write mode is used to be compatible with the mixed use of new and old versions. But the double write mode itself has certain performance problems, so if you can ensure that the version of `@byted-service/metainfo in the project is all> 1.0.2`, then you can use `MetaInfo.turnOffDoubleWrite()` or set the environment variable `METAINFO_DOUBLE_WRITE = false` to turn off double write mode\n\n## Related documents\n\n-   https://bytedance.feishu.cn/space/doc/7a1oB9ln18suyIHU67yfNa\n","scripts":{"test":"ROUTE_IP=10.225.130.44 RUNTIME_IDC_NAME=boe ../../node_modules/.bin/jest --config ./jest.config.json --coverage --env=node","build":"rm -rf lib && ../../node_modules/.bin/tsc","prepublish":"npm run build"},"maintainers":[{"name":"liyubei","avatar":"https://s3-fs.pstatp.com/static-resource/v1/bf5207f4-07f4-4c43-9004-b01af1aff365~?image_size=72x72&cut_type=&quality=&format=png&sticker_format=.webp","email":"liyubei@bytedance.com"},{"name":"nodejs-team","avatar":"","email":"nodejs-team@bnpm.com"},{"name":"qizi","avatar":"https://ee.bytedance.net/ratak/employees/3863359/avatar/?format=noop.png","email":"qizihan@bytedance.com"},{"name":"yeyuanfeng","avatar":"https://s3-fs.pstatp.com/static-resource/v1/43d80005ffccbded38e9~?image_size=72x72&cut_type=&quality=&format=png&sticker_format=.webp","email":"yeyuanfeng@bytedance.com"}],"name":"@byted-service/metainfo","_npmVersion":"lerna/undefined/node@v14.19.3+x64 (linux)","_id":"@byted-service/metainfo@1.1.7","_npmUser":{"email":"nodejs-team@bytedance.com","name":"nodejs-team"},"dist":{"tarball":"https://bnpm.byted.org/@byted-service/metainfo/-/metainfo-1.1.7.tgz","unpackedSize":62198,"fileCount":27,"integrity":"sha512-JCvX9B3qPYke3txrXomd81PGCffJvcADqZ3tkw6tMQqQ9BW2sQgCWTVBfwIB+pDPaKdN8HRJcgyxMhsDxyN1Xg==","shasum":"5eda48a7a713e616ae46e06452fc2ac8124d27fc","size":14097},"license":"MIT","types":"lib/index.d.ts","repository":{"url":"https://cod