eader(key)\n\nConvert `CGI key` to `HTTP Header`.\n\n### MetaInfo.fromHTTPHeader(ctx, h)\n\nObtain `metainfo` from `HTTP Header`.\n\n### MetaInfo.toHTTPHeader(ctx, h)\n\nObtain `HTTP Header` from `metainfo`.\n\n### MetaInfo.withBackwardValues(ctx)\n\nInitialize `backward` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.recvBackwardValue(ctx, key)\n\nGet the `backward` data of the specified `key`.\n\n### MetaInfo.recvAllBackwardValues(ctx)\n\nGet all the `backward` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.setBackwardValue(ctx, key, val)\n\nSet `backward` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.setBackwardValues(ctx, key, val, key, val, ...)\n\nBatch set `backward` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.setBackwardValuesFromMap(ctx, kvs)\n\nBatch set `backward` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.withBackwardValuesToSend(ctx)\n\nInitialize `backward` data ( `send` ).\n\n### MetaInfo.sendBackwardValue(ctx, key, val)\n\nSet `backward` data ( `send` ).\n\n### MetaInfo.sendBackwardValues(ctx, key, val, key, val, ...)\n\nBatch set `backward` data ( `send` ).\n\n### MetaInfo.sendBackwardValuesFromMap(ctx, kvs)\n\nBatch set `backward` data ( `send` ).\n\n### MetaInfo.allBackwardValuesToSend(ctx, kvs)\n\nGet all the `backward` data ( `send` ).\n\n### MetaInfo.turnOffDoubleWrite()\n\nTurn off double write.\n\n### MetaInfo.turnOnDoubleWrite()\n\nTurn on double write.\n\n## Version compatible\n\nIn `version number <= 1.0.2`, the golang metainfo library is not aligned due to historical reasons, and due to its own implementation problems, there are bugs, as follows:\n\n```ts\nimport * as MetaInfo from '@byted-service/metainfo';\n\nconst ctx = {};\n\nMetaInfo.saveTransitValue(ctx, { AAA: 'AAA' });\n\nMetaInfo.getTransitValue(ctx, 'AAA'); // null ???\n```\n\nIn the current version, the dual-write mode is used to be compatible with the mixed use of new and old versions. But the double write mode itself has certain performance problems, so if you can ensure that the version of `@byted-service/metainfo in the project is all> 1.0.2`, then you can use `MetaInfo.turnOffDoubleWrite