tentValue(ctx, k)\n\nDelete the `persistent` data of the specified `key`.\n\n### MetaInfo.transferForward(ctx)\n\nForward pass, used to convert `transient` data from upstream into `transient-upstream` data, and filter out the original `transient-upstream` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.setMetaInfoFromMap(ctx, m)\n\nSave the `metainfo` data in `ctx` to the object for the client to transfer `metainfo` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.saveMetaInfoToMap(ctx, m)\n\nSave the `metainfo` data in the object to `ctx` for the server to receive `metainfo` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.hasMetaInfo(ctx)\n\nDetermine whether there is `metainfo` data in `ctx`.\n\n### MetaInfo.delMetaInfo(ctx)\n\nDelete the `metainfo` data in `ctx`.\n\n### MetaInfo.copyMetaInfo(fromCtx, toCtx)\n\nCopy `metainfo` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.HTTPHeaderToCGIVariable(key)\n\nConvert `HTTP Header` to `CGI key`.\n\n### MetaInfo.CGIVariableToHTTPHeader(key)\n\nConvert `CGI key` to `HTTP Header`.\n\n### MetaInfo.fromHTTPHeader(ctx, h)\n\nObtain `metainfo` from `HTTP Header`.\n\n### MetaInfo.toHTTPHeader(ctx, h)\n\nObtain `HTTP Header` from `metainfo`.\n\n### MetaInfo.withBackwardValues(ctx)\n\nInitialize `backward` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.recvBackwardValue(ctx, key)\n\nGet the `backward` data of the specified `key`.\n\n### MetaInfo.recvAllBackwardValues(ctx)\n\nGet all the `backward` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.setBackwardValue(ctx, key, val)\n\nSet `backward` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.setBackwardValues(ctx, key, val, key, val, ...)\n\nBatch set `backward` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.setBackwardValuesFromMap(ctx, kvs)\n\nBatch set `backward` data.\n\n### MetaInfo.withBackwardValuesToSend(ctx)\n\nInitialize `backward` data ( `send` ).\n\n### MetaInfo.sendBackwardValue(ctx, key, val)\n\nSet `backward` data ( `send` ).\n\n### MetaInfo.sendBackwardValues(ctx, key, val, key, val, ...)\n\nBatch set `backward` data ( `send` ).\n\n### MetaInfo.sendBackwardValuesFromMap(ctx, kvs)\n\nBatch set `backward` data ( `send` ).\n\n### MetaInfo.allBackwardValuesToSend(ctx, kvs)\n\nGet all the `backward` data ( `send` ).\n\n### MetaInfo.turnOffDoubleWrite()\n\nTurn off double write.\n\n### MetaInfo.turnOnDoubleWrite()\n\nTurn on double write.\n\n## Version compatible\n\nIn `version number <= 1.0.2`, the golang metainfo library is not aligned due to historical reasons, and due to its own implementation problems, there are bugs, as follows:\n\n```ts\nimport * as MetaInfo from '@byted-service/metainfo';\n\nconst ctx = {};\n\nMetaInfo.saveTransitValue(ctx, { AAA: 'AAA' });\n\nMetaInfo.getTransitValue(ctx, 'AAA'); // null ???\n```\n\nIn the current version, the dual-write mode is used to be compatible with the mixed use of new and old versions. But the double write mode itself has certain performance problems, so if you can ensure that the version of `@byted-service/metainfo in the project is all> 1.0.2`, then you can use `MetaInfo.turnOffDoubleWrite()` or set the environment variable `METAINFO_DOUBLE_WRITE = false` to turn off double write mode\n\n## Related documents\n\n-   https://bytedance.feishu.cn/space/doc/7a1oB9ln18suyIHU67yfNa\n","name":"@byted-service/metainfo","description":"管理调用链元信息传递的通用模块","devDependencies":{"typescript":"~4.4.4"},"_npmVersion":"lerna/undefined/node@v18.20.4+x64 (linux)","_npmUser":{"name":"nodejs-team","email":"nodejs-team@bytedance.com"}},"1.0.0-alpha.0":{"types":"lib/index.d.ts","scripts":{"test":"RUNTIME_IDC_NAME=lf ../../node_modules/.bin/jest --config ./jest.config.json --coverage --env=node","build":"rm -rf lib && npx tsc","prepublish":"npm run build"},"_nodeVersion":"12.6.0","main":"lib/index.js","license":"ISC","_cnpm_publish_time":1569471486875,"version":"1.0.0-alpha.0","dependencies":{"tslib":"^1.9.3"},"maintainers":[{"email":"liyubei@bytedance.com","name":"liyubei","avatar":"https://s3-fs.pstatp.com/static-resource/v1/bf5207f4-07f4-4c43-9004-b01af1aff365~?image_size=72x72&cut_type=&quality=&format=png&sticker_format=.webp"},{"name":"nodejs-team","avatar":"","email":"nodejs-team@bnpm.com"},{"email":"qi